{"word":"οἰκτείρω","slug":"οἰκτείρω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>οἰκτείρω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:οἶκτος'><el>οἶκτος</el></a>\n<br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, only in <a href='S:present tense'>pres.</a> and <a href='S:imperfect tense'>impf.</a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>to pity, feel pity for, have pity upon</i>, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, attic:— <el>οἰκτ. τινά τινος</el> <i>to pity</i> one <i>for</i> or <i>because of</i> a thing, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>:—also <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> rei, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a>, <el>οἰκτ. νιν λιπεῖν</el> <i>I am sorry</i> to leave her, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}